news.title: The self-made Chinese billionaire battling to save debt-mired Evergrande
news.para: The 62-year-old -- also known as Hui Ka Yan in Cantonese -- was at one point China's richest man, with a taste for luxury labels, exclusive yachts and a nose for praising the Communist Party that steered the economy to a home ownership boom.

news.title: Land acquisition still a major hurdle for Patna metro rail project
news.para: The construction work on the first phase of the project was initiated in September last year. The 6.6-km long elevated metro line (priority corridor) will have five stations from Malahi Pakri to Patliputra ISBT via Khemni Chak and Zero Mile.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board lowers reserve price of 14 commercial units by over 50%
news.para: For instance, the reserve price of a corner booth in Sector 61, Kajheri, has been reduced from Rs 1.14 crore to Rs 56.19 lakh, a decrease of 50.71%. Similarly, the reserve price of a corner booth in Manimajra has dropped from Rs 97.99 lakh to Rs 46.72 lakh, a reduction of 52.32%.

news.title: Soon, a rental housing scheme for industrial workers in Haryana
news.para: Approving the policy proposed by the department of town and country planning (DTCP), the government has asked the department to roll out the scheme in all industrial belts.

news.title: Mumbai: AAI starts enforcing new building height restrictions in Juhu & Dahisar
news.para: Permissible building heights for plots within 1-km radius of the High Frequency transmitter radar at Juhu and within 3-4 km of the High Frequency receiver radar at Dahisar have now reduced drastically.

news.title: Gujarat: Realty registrations spike, as hope lights up residential projects
news.para: As many as 743 real estate projects — residential, commercial, mixed development and plotted schemes — have been registered with the Gujarat Real Estate Regulatory Authority (GujRERA) in 2021-22 as of September 9.

news.title: E-registration of properties to commence from Oct 2: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: “The registration department is ready with the software and the process will be officially rolled out from October 2. This will be for Rera-registered builders who will be given the software by the department after due checks.

news.title: Haryana RERA demands affidavit from Raheja Developers on repair work
news.para: Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (H-Rera) has now directed the developer to submit an affidavit by September 20 with details of the repairs done in the society to date and how the realtor plans to complete the remaining work.

news.title: Gujarat HC seeks reply from Godrej Properties, authorities over 'illegal' shops in society
news.para: The chairman and secretary of Pinecrest Cooperative Housing Service Society Ltd filed a petition in the HC and sought directions to the authorities to seal the 21 shops and return control of these parts of the residential blocks, which are prone to fire, because fire NOCs were never sought for the shops.

news.title: Gurugram: Emerald Hills residents protest over absence of road to society
news.para: The residents said the three 24-metre-wide internal sector roads were in the approved layout plan, but not a single one is operational yet.

news.title: Noida authority plans a drone survey of Supertech twin towers
news.para: A private agency hired by the Noida Authority would carry out the survey of the entire project, but with focus on the Apex and Ceyane towers, which have to be brought down in three months.

news.title: Blackstone scraps $3 billion takeover of Soho China
news.para: Blackstone had hoped to expand its presence in the country through acquisition of Soho China, which holds prime real estate in cities like Beijing.

news.title: Structural stability of some TNHB tenements will be reviewed: Tamil Nadu housing minister
news.para: Briefing reporters after inspecting TNHB's Brindavan Towers complex in K K Nagar in Chennai, the minister said that steps would be taken to redress the issues.

news.title: Amid controversy, Punjab cancels Ludhiana improvement trust's land auction
news.para: On August 16, 29 properties of LIT were auctioned at Rs 129 crore. Of these, a prime land measuring 16,344 square yards was auctioned for Rs 98 crore and it was alleged that its market value was around Rs 350 crore.

news.title: Russian PIK Group's CEO touts possible modular construction IPO
news.para: The creation of the new unit and subsequent share offering could happen in 2023-24, a company spokesperson said.
